ifice, is now presented as pointless slaughter. This shift in tone and content reveals profound changes in Canadian attitudes not only towards the First World War but also towards patriotism, duty, and the shaping of the moral citizen.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aChildren and warzCanada. 0aChildrenzCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aChildrenzCanadaxSocial conditionsy20th century. 0aWorld War, 1914-1918xChildrenzCanada. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Books & Reading.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144269348740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442693487423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442693487.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK